About Me

A glimpse into my mind.

Isiah VanBrackle

Developer

I am a Full Stack Developer. Prior to this I worked at a small security company in client service for four years. My goal in the company was to make sure our clients felt safe and provided for. I consulted them on their itinerary and what add-ons they would need on top of their service. I then managed all the logistics including: organizing with the security team, collecting payment, and collecting data on their experience with the service.
Because of my forays into mechanical engineering and love of robotics I worked on a side project tinkering with drones for the company that re-ignited my interest in programming which inspired me to enter Flatiron School. An experience which nurtured that interest into love.
Now as a Full Stack Developer I’m curious to see what puzzles the tech world holds for me, and excited to solve them.

Languages: Javascript, Ruby, HTML, CSS
Frameworks: Rails, React.js, Redux
Databases: SQL, SQLite, PostgreSQL
Version Control: Git

A Quiet Place

A Book Tracking App

Skills - Google Books API, Rails, JavaScript, React, React-Materialize, React-Router, HTML, CSS
An app that allows people to manage the books they love, and visually track the state of their library.
• Utilized Google Books API to pull data based on the user’s query
• Made POST requests to store data and simultaneously update state
• Passed down state and rendered it so visual library reflects state of user_books table

  • Date: October 2018
  • Frontend
  • Backend

Skills - Rails, JavaScript, HTML, CSS

• Created game logic to shuffle and deal playing cards, upon games initialization
• Built custom API for game, which included card’s suit, nature, and sub-nature

  • Date: September 2018
  • Frontend
  • Backend

Bar Tender

Find the Top 5 Bars Near You

Bar Tender is a command line application. It makes use of the Yelp API to allow a user to find the bars closest to them. A user can store the bars they loved the most after visiting them, and has the freedom to check, update, and delete their favorites as much as they want.

  • Date: August 2018
  • Application
